#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Tebello 'Tibz' Motsoane has been described as generous, kind and genuine. His memorial service was held at Sacred Heart College in Johannesburg on Thursday. The 'chief of cool' was killed in Durban last week. He and his friend Kiernan ‘AKA’ Forbes were gunned down while leaving a Florida Road restaurant. READ: AKA album to be released next week "Tibz was kind, honest and was very genuine, he was gentle," his friend Ziya Sisulu said of him. "These traits he carried in various areas of his life," she added. Sisulu said that Motsoane had the ability to attract people.